  - compose service sets:  user: "1000:1000"   (image default UID 1000001
    overflows the rootless subuid range and fails setresuid)
  - ulimits: nofile soft 2448 / hard 1048576 (Solace POST requires the 1048576
    hard limit). NO memlock key in compose (it breaks `podman exec`); memlock
    comes from a LimitMEMLOCK=infinity drop-in on user@<uid>.service instead.
  - shm_size: 1g
  - a host prerequisite task that creates
    /etc/systemd/system/user@.service.d/solace-limits.conf with
    LimitNOFILE=1048576 / LimitMEMLOCK=infinity / LimitCORE=infinity, then
    restarts user@<uid>.service. (Rootless cannot exceed the user manager
    ceiling, so this must be set BEFORE the broker starts.)
  - a host prerequisite task that, IF podman graphroot/runroot are relocated
    off the default (read storage.conf), applies the matching SELinux fcontext
    equivalence to /var/lib/containers and runs restorecon — otherwise the
    container's libraries fail to load ("cannot change memory protections").
  - storage-group bind-mounted to /var/lib/solace with :Z relabel, owned by the
    mapped container UID.
  - HA redundancy via env keys, driven from group_vars (routername,
    redundancy_enable, redundancy_group_node_<name>_connectvia/_nodetype for
    all three members, redundancy_authentication_presharedkey_key,
    redundancy_activestandbyrole [primary/backup only],
    redundancy_matelink_connectvia [primary/backup only], configsync_enable
